Array factory/Type commenting and new generation
Moved list, finished grow heads, and finished testing

MultiListInt - want to return the Entry, not the actual value in getNextEntryForList (these will many times be the same). Check for nexts not being allocated (if we never add to the same list, return Const.No_ENTRY) in this case.
Adding Typed Collection vs regular Collection interfaces
Int Value Converter can now take an int and convert to other types
Started tests for Hash (need to start deleting bool, others passing).

Changing HashSet test to add/remove with an offset away from zero (to verify that we dont get results around 0 that are unintended)
Started adding Test Utils to complete HashSet tests
Finishing up HashSets, Starting OneToMany tests, and adding packing long and test
Finished up NumberUtil Commenting. Most of OneToManyInt tests done (need copying left).
Started work on implementation of the OneToMany and finishing up some testing
new type of byteslice, keep inserting until we can remove enough to compact, will stay in order.
One to Many work 1/2 way through TDD

One to many, fixed up some disassociation errors. MultiLinkedListInt, on remove of head item, needed to -1 out the heads[next] and next[next] (or else this extra state would point to a potentially valid item and crap out). Caught this from a OneToMany bug that messed up everything. Added test that exposes this, and now compactness is valid on OneToMany. Cleaned up Test assertions, so that expected, actual is in right order.
